@notice Sets the value of a uint256 and locks it such

devdoc.author: brandon@formless.xyz
devdoc.details: Assumes users of the `Immutable` library perform writes using the setters exposed in this contract and not by directly accessing the underlying state variables.
devdoc.title: Immutable state variable library.

insertBooleanAtAddress(Immutable.Address.notice: Inserts an address : bool pair into a map. Once the associated lock for the map is set, subsequent attempts to insert revert.

pushAddress(Immutable.AddressArray stora.notice: Pushes an address value onto an address array. Once the associated lock for the array is set, subsequent attempts to push revert.

pushUnsignedInt256(Immutable.UnsignedInt.notice: Pushes an unsigned 256 integer value onto an unsigned 256 integer array. Once the associated lock for the array is set, subsequent attempts to push revert.

setAddress(Immutable.Address storage,add.notice: Sets the value of an address and locks it such that subsequent attempts to write revert.

setBoolean(Immutable.Boolean storage,boo.notice: Sets the value of a bool and locks it such that subsequent attempts to write revert.

setUnsignedInt256(Immutable.UnsignedInt2.notice: Sets the value of a uint256 and locks it such that subsequent attempts to write revert.

userdoc.notice: Library for contracts to implement write-once post initialization immutable variables. This enables immutable variables that are not initialized in Solidity constructors. By not using parameterized constructors, stable construction parameter invariant runtime bytecode can be generated for the _source code_ associated with all SHARE contracts.
